%md

# 1. Data Exploration (initial)

##### To start, I have an initial view of the data available for the analysis. It consists of transactions for a Product Family of interest, for the timeframe of 01.01.2017 to 28.02.2019. The columns are self-explenatory.

1. Data Exploration (initial)

To start, I have an initial view of the data available for the analysis. It consists of transactions for a Product Family of interest, for the timeframe of 01.01.2017 to 28.02.2019. The columns are self-explenatory.

paragraphs.title: view TRANSACTIONS, initial
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select
    CALENDARDATE as "DATE",
    CUSTOMERNAME as "CUSTOMER",
    AGEGROUP as "AGE GROUP",
    REGION as "REGION",
    GENDER as "GENDER",
    MARITALSTATUS as "MARITAL STATUS",
    EDUCATION as "EDUCATION",
    PROFESSION as "PROFESSION",
    PRODUCTFAMILYNAME as "PRODUCT FAMILY",
    PRODUCTGROUPNAME as "PRODUCT GROUP",
    UNITS as "UNITS",
    UNITARYPRICE as "PRICE",
    GROSSPROFIT as "PROFIT"
from 
    OAC_TRANSACTIONS
order by
    CALENDARDATE;

paragraphs.title: view TRANSACTIONS for CUSTOMER
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select
    CUSTOMERNAME as "CUSTOMER",
    sum(UNITS) as "UNITS",
    sum(UNITS*UNITARYPRICE) as "VALUE",
    sum(GROSSPROFIT) as "PROFIT"
from
    OAC_TRANSACTIONS
group by
    CUSTOMERNAME
order by
    VALUE desc;

paragraphs.title: view TRANSACTIONS for PRODUCT GROUP
paragraphs.text:
%sql

select
    PRODUCTGROUPNAME as "PRODUCT GROUP",
    sum(UNITS) as "UNITS",
    sum(UNITS*UNITARYPRICE) as "VALUE",
    sum(GROSSPROFIT) as "PROFIT"
from
    OAC_TRANSACTIONS
group by
    PRODUCTGROUPNAME
order by
    VALUE desc;

%md

##### Considering the above, I decide that they key for my models needs to be the Customer – Product Group relationship. With regards to parameters to take into account, since I will try to model behaviour in relation to price changes, I will need to build some additional variables. In particular, I will be creating some derived variables for modelling price variation. I decide on 3 month-level variables: one that models the relationship between the current price and the overall average price (long-term price variation), one that models the relationship between the current price and the average price from the past 6 months (medium-term price variation) and one that models the relationship between the current price and last month’s price (short-term price variation). I will also be using additional derived variables.

paragraphs.title: create PRICES table
paragraphs.text:
%sql

create table OML_PRICES
    as select
        concat(substr(CALENDARDATE,7,4),substr(CALENDARDATE,4,2)) as "MONTH",
        PRODUCTGROUPNAME as "PRODUCT GROUP",
        cast(avg(UNITARYPRICE) as numeric(6,2)) as "PRICE"
    from
        OAC_TRANSACTIONS
    group by
        concat(substr(CALENDARDATE,7,4),substr(CALENDARDATE,4,2)),
        PRODUCTGROUPNAME
    order by
        MONTH;

### 2.2.2. Create column AVERAGE PRICE LAST 6 MONTHS
##### The second derived price column holds the average price for the last 6 months. The relation between the current price and the average price for the last 6 months gives us an idea about the influence of medium-term price variation on customer transactions. First I create intermediary tables for average price for the last 6 months calculations for all the months in the scope.

### 2.2.3. Create column AVERAGE PRICE LAST MONTH
##### The third derived price column holds last month’s price. The relation between the current price and last month’s price gives us an idea about the influence of short-term price variation on customer transactions. First I create the dedicated prices table for last month’s price, using the intermediary tables previously created.

2.3. Add columns AVERAGE PRICE(S)

I create an enhanced transactions table, by adding the newly created average price(s) columns. I create the enhanced transactions table, using the intermediary tables previously created.

paragraphs.title: create TRANSACTIONS, enhanced
paragraphs.text:
%script

drop table
    OML_PRICES;
create table OML_TRANSACTIONS
    as select
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."DATE" as "DATE",
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."CUSTOMER" as "CUSTOMER",
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT FAMILY" as "PRODUCT FAMILY",
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT GROUP" as "PRODUCT GROUP",
        max(OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."UNITS") as "UNITS",
        max(OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRICE") as "PRICE",
        max(OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PROFIT") as "PROFIT",
        max(OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRICE TODATE") as "PRICE TODATE",
        max(OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST6M."PRICE LAST6M") as "PRICE LAST6M",
        max(OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST1M."PRICE LAST1M") as "PRICE LAST1M"
    from 
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE
    join 
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST6M on OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."DATE"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST6M."DATE" 
            and OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."CUSTOMER"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST6M."CUSTOMER" 
            and OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT FAMILY"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST6M."PRODUCT FAMILY"
            and OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT GROUP"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST6M."PRODUCT GROUP"
    join 
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST1M on OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."DATE"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST1M."DATE" 
            and OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."CUSTOMER"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST1M."CUSTOMER"
            and OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT FAMILY"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST1M."PRODUCT FAMILY"
            and OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT GROUP"=OML_TRANSACTIONS_LAST1M."PRODUCT GROUP"
    group by
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."DATE", OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."CUSTOMER", OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT FAMILY", OML_TRANSACTIONS_TODATE."PRODUCT GROUP"
    order by
        "DATE", "CUSTOMER";

### 2.4. Add columns DIFFERENCE TO AVERAGE PRICE(S)
#####Using the newly created 3 derived average prices columns, I will be creating 6 additional differences columns. For each of the derived average prices columns, we create an additional 2 differences columns: one representing the difference between the current price and the average price as absolute value, and one representing the difference between the current price and the average price as percentage. This totals to 3 x 2 = 6 additional differences columns. First I create the further enhanced transactions table (I label it as ‘work’ table) by adding the 6 additional calculated columns to the transactions work table.

2.4. Add columns DIFFERENCE TO AVERAGE PRICE(S)

Using the newly created 3 derived average prices columns, I will be creating 6 additional differences columns. For each of the derived average prices columns, we create an additional 2 differences columns: one representing the difference between the current price and the average price as absolute value, and one representing the difference between the current price and the average price as percentage. This totals to 3 x 2 = 6 additional differences columns. First I create the further enhanced transactions table (I label it as ‘work’ table) by adding the 6 additional calculated columns to the transactions work table.

paragraphs.title: create TRANSACTIONS, work
paragraphs.text:
%script

create table OML_TRANSACTIONS_W
    as select
        "DATE" as "DATE",
        "CUSTOMER" as "CUSTOMER",
        "PRODUCT FAMILY" as "PRODUCT FAMILY",
        "PRODUCT GROUP" as "PRODUCT GROUP",
        "UNITS" as "UNITS",
        "PRICE" as "PRICE",
        "PRICE TODATE" as "PRICE TODATE",
        "PRICE"-"PRICE TODATE" as "DIFV TODATE",
        cast(("PRICE"-"PRICE TODATE")*100/"PRICE" as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFP TODATE",
        "PRICE LAST6M" as "PRICE LAST6M",
        "PRICE"-"PRICE LAST6M" as "DIFV LAST6M",
        cast(("PRICE"-"PRICE LAST6M")*100/"PRICE" as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFP LAST6M",
        "PRICE LAST1M" as "PRICE LAST1M",
        "PRICE"-"PRICE LAST1M" as "DIFV LAST1M",
        cast(("PRICE"-"PRICE LAST1M")*100/"PRICE" as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFP LAST1M"
    from
        OML_TRANSACTIONS
    order by
        "DATE", "CUSTOMER";

### 2.5. Aggregate for CUSTOMER and PRODUCT GROUP
##### Because my objective is to model the Customer – Product Group relationship with regards to price changes, I need to aggregate my enhanced transactions work table at Customer and Product Group level. This way, I can leverage the newly created derived columns for average price differences (for long-term, medium-term and short-term) in the Customer – Product Group context to build models that can express the buying behaviour with respect to price changes.
##### I create the aggregated enhanced transactions work table (I label it as ‘aggregated work’ table), by aggregating the enhanced work table on Customer and Product Group.

msg.data:
2.5. Aggregate for CUSTOMER and PRODUCT GROUP

Because my objective is to model the Customer – Product Group relationship with regards to price changes, I need to aggregate my enhanced transactions work table at Customer and Product Group level. This way, I can leverage the newly created derived columns for average price differences (for long-term, medium-term and short-term) in the Customer – Product Group context to build models that can express the buying behaviour with respect to price changes.
I create the aggregated enhanced transactions work table (I label it as ‘aggregated work’ table), by aggregating the enhanced work table on Customer and Product Group.

paragraphs.title: create TRANSACTIONS, work, aggregated
paragraphs.text:
%script

create table OML_TRANSACTIONS_WA
    as select
        "CUSTOMER" as "CUSTOMER",
        "PRODUCT GROUP" as "PRODUCT GROUP",
        sum("UNITS") as "UNITS",
        cast(avg("PRICE") as numeric(6,2)) as "PRICE",
        cast(avg("PRICE TODATE") as numeric(6,2)) as "PRICE TODATE",
        cast(avg("DIFV TODATE") as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFV TODATE",
        cast(avg("DIFP TODATE") as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFP TODATE",
        cast(avg("PRICE LAST6M") as numeric(6,2)) as "PRICE LAST6M",
        cast(avg("DIFV LAST6M") as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFV LAST6M",
        cast(avg("DIFP LAST6M") as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFP LAST6M",
        cast(avg("PRICE LAST1M") as numeric(6,2)) as "PRICE LAST1M",
        cast(avg("DIFV LAST1M") as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFV LAST1M",
        cast(avg("DIFP LAST1M") as numeric(6,2)) as "DIFP LAST1M"
    from
        OML_TRANSACTIONS_W
    group by
        "CUSTOMER", "PRODUCT GROUP";

msg.data:
Table OML_TRANSACTIONS_WA created.


---------------------------

msg.data:
Table OML_TRANSACTIONS_WA dropped.
